claim: A prisoner of war is a person held in custody during or immediately after a meal.
premise_source_doc_sentence: A prisoner of war  (  POW , PoW , PW , P/W , WP , PsW , enemy prisoner of war  (  EPW  )  or `` missing-captured ''  )  is a person , whether combatant or non-combatant , who is held in custody by a belligerent power during or immediately after an armed conflict .
